Riyadh  –  Saudi Arabia’s elderly King Salman on Thursday arrived at the Red Sea region for rest after an operation, the state news agency SPA reported. The 84-year-old monarch left hospital in the capital Riyadh on July 30, after surgery to remove his gallbladder. He will stay in the Neom region in the country’s North-west. Neom is the site of an under-construction futuristic city launched by Saudi Arabia’s powerful Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman in 2017. There has been much speculation about the health of Salman, who has ruled oil-rich Saudi Arabia since 2015. Salman, 34, is seen as the de-facto ruler and the driving force behind opening up of the ultra-conservative monarchy to the outside world and diversifying its oil-reliant economy. (dpa/NAN) RIYADH - King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia, who reigned over the oil-rich Gulf country for nearly a decade, would be buried Friday following the afternoon Islamic prayers. Abdullah, who had been the country's main decision maker since 1995, took over from his predecessor, [pro_ad_display_adzone id="8"] King Fahd when he suffered… January 23, 2015 In "Foreign" •Streets were almost empty in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, on Tuesday. The kingdom’s biggest cities are all under a 24-hour lockdown.Credit...Ahmed Yosri/Reuters By David D. Kirkpatrick and Ben Hubbard The senior Saudi prince who is governor of Riyadh is in intensive care with the coronavirus. Several dozen other members of the… April 8, 2020 In "Foreign" JEDDAH    -     Ethiopia’s Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed and Eritrean President Isaias Afwerki signed a peace agreement in Saudi Arabia on Sunday, the second peace deal reached since July between the once warring African countries. The Ethiopian and Eritrean leaders signed a “joint declaration of peace and friendship” on July… September 17, 2018 In "Foreign"